            <div id="dsq-comment-message-3255" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>Too few people understand and agree with Doctorow&#8217;s &#8220;Evolution is not perfection. Evolution is suitability.&#8221; message. But the reality of evolution is that transhumanistic self-direction is not always sustainable. Doctorow also makes an excellent point about how we do not understand, and therefore cannot qualify, self-identity (yet). An unambiguous and workable definition of self-identity is a prerequisite for possible mind-uploading with confidence.</p>
<p>Thank you, Nikola and Mr. Doctorow, for an enlightening interview!</p>
